<figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6f746884-039a-4111-8538-a49a99b9d4f1_2400x800.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/e3lAEurAKhv_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux. 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/V2U4EZ4ObyTFT9eLHSz6Mx92h- 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/stbkVEwIxo5hnKDGSpo-DMd-L-" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux. 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/HsorzYRJ8Y2X9J2wC_ 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/stbkVEwIxo5hnKDGSpo-DMd-L- 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a></figure><p>I occasionally publish executive briefing papers on arts, media, and culture. (For example, <a href="https://www.honest-broker.com/p/an-executive-briefing-paper-on-the" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">here</a> and <a href="https://www.honest-broker.com/p/why-recording-studios-are-unplugging" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">here</a>.) </p><p>These are quick summaries of important developments you might not hear about elsewhere. If I were advising a Minister of Culture, this is the kind of regular briefing I’d provide. </p><p>But most of us don’t have a Minister of Culture. So let’s act the part ourselves.</p><h4><em>The Honest Broker </em>is a reader-supported guide to music, books, media &amp; culture. Both free and paid subscriptions are available. If you want to support my work, the best way is by taking out a paid subscription.</h4><p><a href="https://www.honest-broker.com/subscribe?" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Subscribe now</a></p><h3>Half of Waking Hours Are Now Devoted to Entertainment</h3><p>Are you not entertained?</p><p>If not, you just have yourself to blame. Your neighbors now spend most of their waking hours getting entertained, <a href="https://luminatedata.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">according to research outfit Luminate</a>.</p><p>This number has grown 22% in the last year. </p><p>How is this even possible? Don’t people have jobs? Don’t they have family obligations? Don’t they. . . have a life? </p><p>Maybe not. But who cares, just so long as the TikTok videos keep reeling.</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F85089a4e-4f9f-4b0c-aca3-f362fea8c2f0_2400x1254.png" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux. 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/2VZHC193sOX4VmCX6FDoguDy0w- 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/T7bXYXmZWCs5fPbJJXNkafn- 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/5G- 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux." alt="Infographic showing that half of waking hours are devoted to entertainment" title="Infographic showing that half of waking hours are devoted to entertainment" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/QFvCLmNmZZvn8d7u57wM2Q_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/VaMP174aLUodU- 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux. 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a></figure><p><strong>An unanswered question:</strong> If entertainment is most of modern life, why don’t artists and creators make more money? Meanwhile the <em>Forbes</em> billionaire list is filled with people who create the <em>infrastructure</em> for all this diversion. Surely creation is a more useful skill in entertainment than distribution, no? </p><h3>Artists Really Are Getting Poorer</h3><p>Many of my readers already knew this. But now we have some numbers to measure the pain and suffering.</p><p><a href="https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=4565123" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">According to Christos Makridis of Stanford</a>:</p><blockquote><p>I find a decline in the relative earnings of artists to non-artists from zero to a 15% disadvantage. After controlling for demographic differences, the decline is sharper, declining from a 15% earnings disadvantage to 30%….</p><p>When restricting the set of individuals to those with at least a college degree, those with a fine arts degree also incur an earnings and employment penalty even if they work in the arts. These results highlight the increasing financial precariousness of artists over the past decade.</p></blockquote><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff10a58be-3f24-4166-8411-8a260209726c_1692x1144.png" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/3-bD86HV-ryJBGHVIrtCqI9zxHZ8kl_Tn0J1cckz9kE=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd180MjQsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkZmMTBhNThiZS0zZjI0LTQxNjYtODQxMS04YTI2MDIwOTcyNmNfMTY5MngxMTQ0LnBuZw== 424w, https://reader.miniflux. 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/vuB-wSc7TGV8vRYlSHMftNi0mOoP-VHOMLYZ1t0i_ao=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xNDU2LGNfbGltaXQsZl93ZWJwLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGZjEwYTU4YmUtM2YyNC00MTY2LTg0MTEtOGEyNjAyMDk3MjZjXzE2OTJ4MTE0NC5wbmc= 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/qfpPA5g0jioAXEqFya1